  "elapsed_s": 108.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was one of those relatively few towns in Hungary where the Jewish population, other than in Budapest-- where, of course, over a quarter of the population was Jewish-- where there was such a heavy concentration of Jewish population and where the impact of the Jewish community was as substantial as it was in Kisvarda.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Almost all of commerce [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] professions-- banking, what little manufacturing there was, and other than the schools, I would say all of cultural life, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] including the lending libraries-- which is the only kind of libraries that were in town; there were no public libraries-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] were completely Jewishly dominated.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The Jewish community itself was a very interesting and composite community.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was entirely Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But, of course, the actual population, Jewish population, wasn't Orthodox by any means.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were both various shading of observance as well as various shadings of assimilation, various degrees of assimilation.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But formally, the community was Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And, as a matter of fact, I would say that the community was, by and large, dominated by the fundamentalist or the extreme Orthodox, mostly Hasidic community.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] In, in its public behavior, the community had to conform to the [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] positions basically-- or observance basically [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] prescribed by the Ultra Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I don't know for sure whether or not numerically they also constituted the majority, although it could have been because as, as usual in-- with orthodox communities, their birth rate, of course, was much higher than that of the non-orthodox or non-observant or assimilated Jews.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So it is quite possible that, that they constituted the majority.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
